        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c133",
          "text": "“For wholeness — the basis of health — we need nourishment at every level. The complex and dynamic organisation of the physical body underpins our relationship to spatial qualities. Life enhancing qualities around us support our life energies. Colour, harmony, muli-sensory delight support our feeling life, particular moods redressing personal and situational imbalances. … Buildings built upon these principles are buildings to nurture the whole human being.” — Christopher Day (2002, p.187).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 461,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "PQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f3cb",
          "text": "David Pearson, founder of the Ecological Design Association in the UK and co-founder of Gaia International, an innovative group of ecologically responsible and inspired architects, believes that “far from expensive technological dreams, we need a down to earth vision — a future home integrated into a sustainable lifestyle for all of us.” He argues: “Whether old or new, future housing will need to employ life-supporting systems. Materials, and spatial designs that meet the health, conservation and spiritual criteria” (Pearson, 1998, p.57) listed in the ‘Gaia House Charter’.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 536,
              "href": "https://books.google.es/books/about/The_New_Natural_House_Book.html?id=pX1gOd6DRmoC&redir_esc=y",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 523,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "43a5",
          "text": "This is a list of criteria for holistic sustainable building that was drawn up by the members of Gaia International; it is summarised in the table below (see Table 4.2). Many such houses have already been built and many old existing structures have been converted with these principles in mind. These are the beginnings of a complete transformation of the existing building stock to meet the long-term requirements of sustainable living.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8201",
          "text": "The Gaia House Charter for Healthy and Sustainable Building",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 59,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 59,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "47ef",
          "text": "(Reproduced and adapted from Pearson, 1998, p.57)",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c430",
          "text": "Designing for Harmony with the Planet:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 38,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b40c",
          "text": "Site, orient, and shelter the home to make best and conserving use of renewable resources. Use the sun, wind, and water for all or most of your energy needs and rely less on supplementary non-renewable energy",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "41aa",
          "text": "Use green materials and products — non-toxic, non-polluting, sustainable, and renewable, produced with low energy and low environmental costs, and biodegradable or easily reused and recycled.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2714",
          "text": "Design the house to be intelligent in its use of resources and complement natural mechanisms, if necessary with efficient control systems to regulate, heating, cooling, water, airflow and lighting.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_12",
          "href": null,
          "name": "336a",
          "text": "Integrate the house with the local ecosystem, by planting indigenous tree and flower species.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8924",
          "text": "Compost organic wastes, garden organically, and use natural pest control — no pesticides.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7dd5",
          "text": "Recycle greywater and use low-flush or waterless toilets. Collect, store, and use rainwater",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1c28",
          "text": "Design systems to prevent export of pollution to the air, water, and soil",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "99fb",
          "text": "Designing for Peace and Spirit:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 31,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "64ba",
          "text": "Make the home harmonious with its environment — blending in with the community, the building styles, scale and materials around it.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b0a0",
          "text": "Participate with others at every scale, using personal ideas and skills of all in order to seek a holistic living design",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "789b",
          "text": "Use proportions, forms and shapes that are harmonious, creating beauty and tranquillity.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a110",
          "text": "Use colours and textures of natural materials and natural dyes, paints, stains to create a personal and therapeutic colour environment.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_21",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1ded",
          "text": "Site and design the house to be life enhancing, and increase the wellbeing or vital force chi, of its occupants.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 93,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 90,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_22",
          "href": null,
          "name": "53e9",
          "text": "Connect the home with Gaia and the natural world and the rhythms and cycles of the Earth, its seasons, and its days.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_23",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2c5b",
          "text": "Make the home a healing environment in which the mind and the spirit can be free and flourish",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_24",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5c9e",
          "text": "Designing for Health of the Body:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 33,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_25",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1cfe",
          "text": "Create a healthy indoor climate by allowing the house to breathe, and use natural materials and processes to regulate temperature, airflow and quality.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_26",
          "href": null,
          "name": "54aa",
          "text": "Site the home away from harmful EM [electro-magnetic] radiation from power lines and also away from negative ground radiation. Design to prevent the build-up of static and EMF [electro- magnetic fields] from domestic equipment, and to avoid interference with beneficial cosmic and terrestrial radiation.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_27",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5d59",
          "text": "Provide safe and healthy air and water, free from pollutants (radon especially), with good humidity, negative-ion balance, and pleasant fragrance from herbs, materials, and polishes. Use natural airflow and ventilation.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_28",
          "href": null,
          "name": "9a08",
          "text": "Create a quiet home, protect and insulate from external and internal noise, and a pleasant, sound- healthy environment.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_29",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c3c0",
          "text": "Design to allow sunlight and daylight to penetrate, and thus rely less on artificial lighting.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "57c43e2e307a_30",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c1eb",
          "text": "… [this is an excerpt from the ‘Ecological Design Dimension’ of Gaia Education’s online course in ‘Design for Sustainability’. Your can enroll in this course at any time. The next instalment of the ‘Ecological Dimension’ will start in mid January 2020. The material in this dimension was co-authored by Lisa Shaw, Michael Shaw, Ezio Gorio, and Daniel Christian Wahl, author of ‘Designing Regenerative Cultures’ and Head of Innovation and (Programme) Design at Gaia Education.]",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
